[The number of measles cases in Pima County, Arizona, (representing
now the largest measles outbreak in the country) has progressed from
a single imported case to the 1st local case on 7 Mar 2008 to 9 cases
on 31 Mar to the present 16 confirmed cases -- some of whom represent
4th generation cases, and 5th generation cases are now expected. The
number of susceptibles (unvaccinated, partially vaccinated, and the
immune-compromised) in the community appears to be sufficient to
sustain an escalating outbreak that may only be contained by a
comprehensive vaccination response.

The HealthMap/ProMED-mail interactive map at
<http://healthmap.org/promed?v=40,-97.6,4>
can be used to locate the state of Arizona. Pima County can be
located on the county map at
<http://www.rootsweb.ancestry.com/~azgila/comap.htm>. - Mod.CP]
